<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1149,2041]" pageId="9" pageNumber="470">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,459,1402,1428]" pageId="9" pageNumber="470">External morphology.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[465,672,1403,1428]" class="Demospongiae" family="Acarnidae" genus="Iophon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Poecilosclerida" pageId="9" pageNumber="470" phylum="Porifera" rank="subSpecies" species="situ" subSpecies="appearance">
<emphasis box="[465,672,1403,1428]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="470">In situ appearance</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[686,833,1402,1429]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1184,1209]" captionTargetBox="[151,1474,409,1165]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1474,409,1165]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hemigellius pilosus (Kirkpatrick, 1907) BELUM.Mc2015.608.A. In situ appearance. B. Close up of branch In situ. C. Skeleton, scale 1000 µm. D. Oxea, scale 500 µm. E. Sigma, scale 10 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3376034/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="470">Figure 3A, B</figureCitation>
): Beige branched sponge with flattened branches. The largest of our three specimens was over 
<quantity box="[605,674,1438,1465]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="470" unit="cm" value="30.0">30 cm</quantity>
in height and the smallest was around 
<quantity box="[1114,1188,1438,1465]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="470" unit="cm" value="10.0">10 cm</quantity>
. Branches are 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="9" pageNumber="470" unit="cm" value="1.0" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="0.5">0.5–1.5 cm</quantity>
maximum diameter. The branching pattern is irregular with some branches dividing into two and others several fingers which may be webbed together. Often the branches are rounded at their tips but some are pointed—this seems to be when new divisions are starting off.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1149,2041]" pageId="9" pageNumber="470">
<emphasis box="[199,461,1582,1608]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="470">Preserved appearance.</emphasis>
Soft grey branched sponge with softly hispid surface. Ends of skeletal fibres project about 
<quantity box="[220,334,1617,1645]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="470" unit="mm" value="0.75" valueMax="1.0" valueMin="0.5">0.5–1 mm</quantity>
beyond the ectosome.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1149,2041]" pageId="9" pageNumber="470">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,302,1653,1680]" pageId="9" pageNumber="470">Skeleton</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[317,433,1654,1680]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1184,1209]" captionTargetBox="[151,1474,409,1165]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1474,409,1165]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hemigellius pilosus (Kirkpatrick, 1907) BELUM.Mc2015.608.A. In situ appearance. B. Close up of branch In situ. C. Skeleton, scale 1000 µm. D. Oxea, scale 500 µm. E. Sigma, scale 10 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3376034/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="470">Figure 3C</figureCitation>
): Columns of 3–4 oxea joined by single spicules. Fanning slightly at surface. Projecting ends of columns form surface hispidation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1149,2041]" pageId="9" pageNumber="470">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,297,1725,1752]" pageId="9" pageNumber="470">Spicules</emphasis>
: Oxeas (
<figureCitation box="[397,517,1726,1752]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1184,1209]" captionTargetBox="[151,1474,409,1165]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1474,409,1165]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hemigellius pilosus (Kirkpatrick, 1907) BELUM.Mc2015.608.A. In situ appearance. B. Close up of branch In situ. C. Skeleton, scale 1000 µm. D. Oxea, scale 500 µm. E. Sigma, scale 10 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3376034/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="470">Figure 3D</figureCitation>
): 
<collectionCode box="[537,637,1725,1752]" country="United Kingdom" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/2x42-q9ch" name="Ulster Museum, Belfast" pageId="9" pageNumber="470">BELUM</collectionCode>
.Mc2015.608 491(523)566 by 24(28) 
<quantity box="[1051,1127,1726,1753]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.4" pageId="9" pageNumber="470" unit="mm" value="34.0">34 µm</quantity>
; 
<collectionCode box="[1139,1239,1725,1752]" country="United Kingdom" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/2x42-q9ch" name="Ulster Museum, Belfast" pageId="9" pageNumber="470">BELUM</collectionCode>
.Mc2015.784 Oxeas 368(409)439 by 14(19) 
<quantity box="[454,528,1762,1789]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="9" pageNumber="470" unit="mm" value="23.0">23 µm</quantity>
</paragraph>
