<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1149,2041]" lastBlockId="10.[151,1437,153,395]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="471" pageId="9" pageNumber="470">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1834,1860]" pageId="9" pageNumber="470">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kirkpatrick, R." box="[323,527,1834,1860]" pageId="9" pageNumber="470" pagination="271 - 291" refId="ref35517" refString="Kirkpatrick, R. (1907) Preliminary Report on the Monaxonellida of the National Antarctic Expedition. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Series 7, 20 (117), 271 - 291. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222930709487333" type="journal article" year="1907">Kirkpatrick (1907</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kirkpatrick, R." box="[539,596,1834,1860]" pageId="9" pageNumber="470" pagination="1 - 56" refId="ref35564" refString="Kirkpatrick, R. (1908) Porifera (Sponges). II. Tetraxonida. National Antarctic Expedition, 1901 - 1904. Natural History, 4, 1 - 56." type="journal article" year="1908">1908</bibRefCitation>
) described this species as an ‘erect flattened triangular or elongate lamella divided or digitate at the upper edges’ with a ‘finely conulose and pilose’ surface. The skeleton consists of primary fibres 2–5 spicules thick joined by secondary fibres usually one but sometimes two or three thick. The oxea are 537 by 
<quantity box="[241,317,1942,1969]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="9" pageNumber="470" unit="mm" value="23.0">23 µm</quantity>
and sigmas 
<quantity box="[464,540,1942,1969]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.9" pageId="9" pageNumber="470" unit="mm" value="39.0">39 µm</quantity>
in length and 
<quantity box="[711,787,1942,1969]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="9" pageNumber="470" unit="mm" value="16.0">16 µm</quantity>
in breadth (our measurements from the 
<typeStatus box="[1257,1359,1942,1968]" pageId="9" pageNumber="470">holotype</typeStatus>
: styles 550(562)640 by 20(27) 
<quantity box="[416,493,1977,2005]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="9" pageNumber="470" unit="mm" value="35.0">35 µm</quantity>
, sigmas 30(36) 
<quantity box="[677,755,1978,2005]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="470" unit="mm" value="40.0">40 µm</quantity>
. The spicule dimensions and form, skeletal form and external form of our specimens are a good match for the type specimen although the oxea in 
<collectionCode box="[1147,1247,2013,2040]" country="United Kingdom" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/2x42-q9ch" name="Ulster Museum, Belfast" pageId="9" pageNumber="470">BELUM</collectionCode>
.Mc2015.784 are slightly shorter. 
<bibRefCitation author="Hajdu, E. &amp; Fonseca, C. &amp; Schories, D. &amp; Kohlberg, G." box="[336,553,153,180]" pageId="10" pageNumber="471" pagination="56 - 78" refId="ref35122" refString="Hajdu, E., Fonseca, C., Schories, D. &amp; Kohlberg, G. (2016) Sponges, Porifera. In: Schories, D. &amp; Kohlberg, G. (Eds.), Marine Wildlife, King George Island, Antarctica: Identification guide. Dirk Schories publications, Rostock, pp. 56 - 78." type="book chapter" year="2016">
Hajdu 
<emphasis box="[413,470,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="471">et al.</emphasis>
(2016)
</bibRefCitation>
recently reported a specimen from 
<quantity box="[961,1019,153,179]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="471" unit="m" value="40.0">40 m</quantity>
in the South 
<collectingRegion box="[1175,1364,153,179]" country="United Kingdom" name="Shetland Islands" pageId="10" pageNumber="471">Shetland Islands</collectingRegion>
. Their figured specimen has a slightly different form to ours with more elongate branches and is reported as being dark yellow to orange in colour.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,153,395]" pageId="10" pageNumber="471">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,260,287]" pageId="10" pageNumber="471">Distribution.</emphasis>
This species was originally described from the Ross Sea in 
<quantity box="[1022,1121,260,287]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.05" metricValueMax="5.5" metricValueMin="4.6" pageId="10" pageNumber="471" unit="m" value="50.5" valueMax="55.0" valueMin="46.0">46–55 m</quantity>
and has since been reported from the South 
<collectingRegion box="[328,513,297,323]" country="United Kingdom" name="Shetland Islands" pageId="10" pageNumber="471">Shetland Islands</collectingRegion>
in 
<quantity box="[550,608,297,323]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="471" unit="m" value="40.0">40 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Hajdu, E. &amp; Fonseca, C. &amp; Schories, D. &amp; Kohlberg, G." box="[623,826,297,324]" pageId="10" pageNumber="471" pagination="56 - 78" refId="ref35122" refString="Hajdu, E., Fonseca, C., Schories, D. &amp; Kohlberg, G. (2016) Sponges, Porifera. In: Schories, D. &amp; Kohlberg, G. (Eds.), Marine Wildlife, King George Island, Antarctica: Identification guide. Dirk Schories publications, Rostock, pp. 56 - 78." type="book chapter" year="2016">
Hajdu 
<emphasis box="[701,758,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="471">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
), Ross Sea (
<bibRefCitation author="Brueggeman, P." box="[963,1193,297,323]" pageId="10" pageNumber="471" refId="ref34246" refString="Brueggeman, P. (1998) Porifera-Demospongiae: demosponges. In: Brueggeman, P. (Ed.), Underwater Field Guide to Ross Island &amp; McMurdo Sound, Antarctica. Available from: http: // peterbrueggeman. com / nsf / fguide / index. html (accessed 12 December 2018)" type="url" year="1998">Brueggeman (1998)</bibRefCitation>
; Ocean Survey 20/20 (2013); 
<bibRefCitation author="Mangano, S. &amp; Michaud, L. &amp; Caruso, C. &amp; Giudice, A." box="[239,496,333,359]" pageId="10" pageNumber="471" pagination="227 - 235" refId="ref35955" refString="Mangano, S., Michaud, L., Caruso, C. &amp; Giudice, A. (2014) Metal and antibiotic resistance in psychotropic bacteria associated with the Antarctic sponge Hemigellius pilosus (Kirkpatrick, 1907). Polar Biology, 37, 227 - 235. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 00300 - 013 - 1426 - 1" type="journal article" year="2014">
Mangano 
<emphasis box="[351,406,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="471">et al.</emphasis>
(2014))
</bibRefCitation>
and the South Pacific (
<bibRefCitation author="NIWA" box="[749,889,333,360]" pageId="10" pageNumber="471" refId="ref36163" refString="NIWA (2016) Vulnerable marine ecosystems in the South Pacific Ocean region. National Institute of Water and Atmospheric Research (NIWA), Wellington, New Zealand, 202873 records. Available from: http: // nzobisipt. elasticbeanstalk. com / resource. do? r = vme _ inverts (accessed 12 December 2018)" type="url" year="2016">NIWA 2016</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Burton, M." box="[906,1064,333,359]" pageId="10" pageNumber="471" pagination="393 - 458" refId="ref34303" refString="Burton, M. (1929) British Antarctic (' Terra Nova') Expedition, 1910. Natural History Report. Porifera: Part II: Antarctic Sponges. Zoology, 6, 393 - 458." type="journal article" year="1929">Burton (1929)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName authority="Gray, 1867" authorityName="Kirkpatrick" authorityYear="1908" box="[1197,1309,333,359]" class="Demospongiae" family="Chalinidae" genus="Gellius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="10" pageNumber="471" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="pilosus">
<emphasis box="[1197,1309,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="471">H. pilosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Topsent 1901)" authorityName="Topsent" authorityYear="1901" baseAuthorityName="Topsent" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[182,643,369,395]" class="Demospongiae" family="Chalinidae" genus="Haliclona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="10" pageNumber="471" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="rudis" subGenus="Gellius">
<emphasis box="[182,294,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="471">Haliclona</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[310,391,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="471">Gellius</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[407,465,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="471">rudis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Topsent, E." box="[479,635,369,395]" pageId="10" pageNumber="471" pagination="5 - 16" refId="ref37618" refString="Topsent, E. (1901) Notice preliminaire sur les eponges recueuillies par l'Expedition Antarctique Belge. Archives de Zoologie experimentale et generale, 3, 5 - 16." type="journal article" year="1901">Topsent 1901</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, however, he later revised this (
<bibRefCitation author="Burton, M." box="[998,1144,369,395]" pageId="10" pageNumber="471" pagination="237 - 392" refId="ref34378" refString="Burton, M. (1932) Sponges. Discovery Reports, 6, 237 - 392. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 24379" type="journal article" year="1932">Burton 1932</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
